        <updateDate>2021-04-21T12:37:31Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Modern Worker Empowerment Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the use of common law rules for defining an <i>employee</i> under the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938. Generally, an individual is an employee under common law rules when an employer controls what work will be done and how it will be done, among other factors.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
